    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Elian in Havana: Let the Healing Begin</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Miller letter hopes that Elian Gonzalez's return to Cuba with his father will presage visit by Miami relatives who sought to keep child in US, as part of 'healing' process (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Justices Allow Cuban Boy to Fly Home'' (front page, June 29):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Justices Allow Cuban Boy to Fly Home'' (front page, June 29):</p>
        <p>It is to be hoped that Elian Gonzalez's peaceful return with his father to his homeland will presage a visit to Cuba by his Miami relatives as part of the healing process this little boy has begun. Now is not the time to dwell on the agony of defeat or to celebrate a political victory but for both sides to work toward reconciliation and together build a better future for the thousands of other innocent Cuban children caught in a political battle that was not of their making.</p>
        <p>TOM MILLER  Oakland, Calif., June 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
